'''Samir El Mourabet''' ({{langx|ar|سمير المرابط}}; born 6 October 2005) is a professional [[association football|football]] player who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]]. Born in France, he represents the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Club career==
El Mourabet joined the youth academy of [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] as a youth, before switching to [[futsal]] with [[Olympique Lyonnais|Lyon Futsal]], returning to Strasbourg in 2022. On 6 January 2024, he made his senior and professional debut with Strasbourg in a 4–0 [[Coupe de France]] win over [[Avoine OCC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Samir-el-mourabet-va-signer-pro-a-strasbourg/1467728|title=Samir El Mourabet va signer pro à Strasbourg|website=L'Équipe}}</ref> On 27 May 2024, he signed his first professional contract with Strasbourg until 2027.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/samir-el-mourabet-signe-professionnel-39535542|title=Samir El Mourabet signe professionnel|date=20 August 2025|website=OneFootball}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, El Mourabet is of Moroccan descent. He played for the [[France national futsal team|France Futsal U19s]] in 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.fff.fr/article/97-four-in-a-row-for-les-bleuets-.html|title=Four in a row for Les Bleuets!|website=uk.fff.fr}}</ref> He is a youth international for Morocco, having played for the [[Morocco national under-20 football team|Morocco U20]]s starting in 2023.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sport7.ma/%d9%85%d9%88%d9%87%d8%a8%d8%a9-%d9%85%d8%ba%d8%b1%d8%a8%d9%8a%d8%a9-%d8%ac%d8%af%d9%8a%d8%af%d8%a9-%d8%b8%d9%87%d8%b1%d8%aa-%d9%87%d8%b0%d8%a7-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%a3%d8%b3%d8%a8%d9%88%d8%b9-%d9%81%d9%8a/|title=موهبة مغربية جديدة ظهرت هذا الأسبوع في الدوري الفرنسي|first=زكرياء نايت|last=همو|date=18 August 2025}}</ref>

